    People also ask
    What country is the Atalanta soccer team from?
    Italy
    Atalanta is based in Bergamo, Lombardy, Italy and has played its home matches at the Gewiss Stadium since 1928. It currently competes in Serie A, the top tier of the Italian football league system.

    Description

    Atalanta Bergamasca Calcio, commonly referred to as Atalanta, is a professional football club based in Bergamo, Lombardy, Italy, who compete in Serie A, the top tier of the Italian league system. Wikipedia
    Manager: Gian Piero Gasperini
    Location: Bergamo
    Leagues: UEFA Champions League, Serie A, Coppa Italia
    Arena/Stadium: Gewiss Stadium
    Capacity: 24,950
    Founded: 17 October 1907; 117 years ago as SBG Atalanta; 30 March 1920; 104 years ago as Atalanta Bergamasca Calcio
